    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1725"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1725">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.124/10.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of the
                            Treasury</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to your letters of
                    April 24 and May 4, 1912, relative to the request made by the President of Peru
                    [etc.]</p>
                <p>The Department is informed by the Surgeon General of the Public Health and Marine
                    Hospital Service that Acting Assistant Surgeon G. M. Converse of that Service is
                    professionally qualified for this duty, speaks the Spanish language, and is
                    available for the said duty. Dr. Converse is willing to accept the position on
                    the following terms: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>His traveling expenses to and from Iquitos to be paid by the Peruvian
                            Government.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>His traveling expenses while engaged in this sanitary work to be paid
                            by the Peruvian Government.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>His compensation to be 100 pounds sterling a month.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>The tenure of office to be fixed at no less than two years.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>In the event that the Peruvian Government decides to accept the services of the
                    above-mentioned officer this Department will grant him the necessary leave of
                    absence.</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Curtis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
